snippet: At least 13 Libyan soldiers were killed and more than 70 were wounded Thursday in car bombings and clashes with Islamists near the airport in the eastern city of Benghazi, military officials said.
abstract: Military officials say at least 13 Libyan soldiers are killed and more than 70 are wounded in car bombings and clashes with Islamists near the airport in the eastern city of Benghazi.
lead_paragraph: At least 13 Libyan soldiers were killed and more than 70 were wounded Thursday in car bombings and clashes with Islamists near the airport in the eastern city of Benghazi, military officials said.

headline.main: Libya: Islamist Militias Batter Soldiers Near Benghazi
